<P><BR>

<DIV ALIGN=LEFT><H1><FONT COLOR="RED">Gardening Questions?<BR>
</FONT></H1></DIV>

<DIV ALIGN=LEFT><H2><FONT COLOR="RED">Visit one of these
sites.</FONT></H2></DIV>

<P></P><BR>


<TT>(C) Copyright: City Farmer 1995</TT>

<P>

<BLOCKQUOTE>There is a fantastic variety of gardening material on the
Internet. From bamboo sellers to rose club members, gardeners are
thrilled to share their knowledge. Some sites have become mini,
annotated indexes of where to find what you are looking for.

<B>Urban Agriculture Notes</B> is not set up to answer your horticulture
questions, so try surfing these wavey sites. </BLOCKQUOTE>


<P><BR>


<A HREF="http://trine.com/GardenNet/"><FONT SIZE=4> <IMG
SRC="gardenet.GIF" ALIGN=left  WIDTH="193" HEIGHT="73" HSPACE=5
VSPACE=5></FONT></A>

A garden center for garden enthusiasts by Cheryl M. Trine. "We all start
gardening in ignorance. If we're generous and lucky, we may one day have
the chance to look back on a lifetime of gardening and realize that
fellow gardeners were our teachers and friends." <A
HREF="http://trine.com/GardenNet/"><FONT SIZE=4><B>GardenNet</B></FONT></A>
includes pages titled<B> What's New, Gardens On-line, Catalog Center,
GardenNet Magazine, Travel & Vacation, Garden Associations, Events
Calendar, Books & Multimedia, Internet Resources, and Visitor's
Center</B>.




<P><BR>


<A HREF="http://www.prairienet.org/ag/garden/homepage.htm"><FONT
SIZE=4><IMG SRC="gardgate.GIF" ALIGN=left  WIDTH="203" HEIGHT="142"
HSPACE=5 VSPACE=5>

<B>The Garden Gate </B></FONT></A>by Karen Fletcher offers gardeners and nature
lovers links to useful and interesting sites around the world as well as
a growing collection of original materials. So if you enjoy plants,
either in the garden or in nature, stop on by, the gate is open! The
Garden Gate is provided as a non-commercial service for the enjoyment
and edification of recreational gardeners everywhere. It includes such
links as <B>What's Coming into Bloom, The Garden Spider's Web, and The
Teaching Garden.</B>


<P><BR>

<A
HREF="http://www.pathfinder.com/@@GK2PJOGhBQEAQORA/vg/Welcome/welcome.html"><FONT
