Vancouver sells worm bins, wrigglers included at half price." (Kitchen
Help: Wrigglers Under the Sink, page 76)<P>



<DT><B><A HREF="ratincompost5.html#rats"><FONT SIZE=4>Dealing With a Rat
in a Compost Bin</FONT></A></B> <DD>An individual who calls the Compost
Hotline is usually quite shocked that he has a rat on his property.

<P>


<DT><B><A HREF="communitygarden7.html#community"><FONT SIZE=4>Community
Gardens.</FONT></A></B> <DD>By far the largest collection of information
on this subject can be found amongst the membership of the American
Community Garden Association (ACGA)

