<HTML> <HEAD>

<title>City Farmer: Compost Module</title> </HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="blue_background.GIF">

<BLOCKQUOTE>

<DIV ALIGN=CENTER><A NAME="module"><IMG SRC="CityFarmerBanner.GIF"
ALT="GFUAbanner" ALIGN=middle WIDTH="400" HEIGHT="30"></A> <BR>


<H5><FONT COLOR="Navy">Published by City Farmer, Canada's Office of
Urban Agriculture</FONT></H5></DIV>

<P><BR>

<DIV ALIGN=LEFT><H1><FONT COLOR="RED">Compost
Module</A></FONT></H1></DIV>

<DIV ALIGN=LEFT><H2><FONT COLOR="RED">Composting Activities For
Children</FONT></H2></DIV>

<P></P><BR>

<IMG ALIGN=right WIDTH="268" HEIGHT="180" BORDER=2 HSPACE=10 VSPACE-10
SRC="wigglworm.GIF" ALT="worm grahic"></CENTER> <P>







<P> Developed in Vancouver, British Columbia by a team of compost
educators as an addendum to the popular Eco Education Program, the
Compost Module will help bring children, teachers, parents and the
community into the compost picture.

<P> Through a number of engaging activities, children (K-7) learn that
composting is a personal and social responsibility. They learn how much
garbage they produce, what it's made up of and how to reduce, reuse and
recycle it through composting.

<P> A light-hearted video (optional), entitled <B>Do the Compost
Scene</B>, gives composting the good rap it deserves and introduces
students to the basics. Teacher directed activities in the module range
from making <B>Compost in a Cup</B> to comparing <B>Apples and
Oranges</B>. Field trips, question and answer sessions and a variety of
experiments on the <B>Fine Art of Decay</B> will keep students absorbed
for many happy hours.

<P> <TABLE BORDER=2 WIDTH=80% >

<TR> <TD>Compost Module Package <BR>(includes booklet, video and poster)
</TD><TD ALIGN=RIGHT>$29.95</TD> </TR>

<TR> <TD>Shipping and Handling from Canada </TD><TD ALIGN=RIGHT>$6.00
Can.</TD> </TR>

<TR> <TD>Shipping and Handling from the United States </TD><TD
ALIGN=RIGHT>$10.00 US.</TD> </TR>


</TABLE>

<P> Order From:<BR><TT> Spring Gillard <BR>#1004-2476 York Avenue
<BR>Vancouver, B.C. V6K 1E2 <BR>Phone: (604) 736-8406 </TT><BR> Please
make cheques payable to Spring Gillard.


