<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Sussex Chemistry Research</TITLE></HEAD>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" text="#000000">
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="/images/cpes.gif">   
<H2>Current Research at Sussex.</H2>
</CENTER>
<P>The Chemistry subject group provides a focus for research in
chemistry and chemistry-related subjects. It comprises 28 academic
faculty, about 30 research faculty and 100 postgraduates. There are
several active emeritus, honorary and visiting faculty.</P><H2>Areas of
Research.</H2><BASEFONT SIZE="+2"><UL>
<LI><A HREF="esres.html">Environmental Science</A></LI>
<LI><A HREF="iores.html">Inorganic and Organometallic Chemistry</A></LI>
<LI><A HREF="omres.html">Organic and Medicinal Chemistry</A></LI>
<LI><A HREF="pccpres.html">Physical Chemistry and Chemical Physics</A></LI>
<LI><A HREF="polyres.html">Polymer Science</A></LI></UL></BASEFONT>
<P>
<H2>Research Groups Home Pages.</H2>
<P><BASEFONT SIZE="+2">
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="/resgrps/sjc/welcome.html">The Caddick Group</A>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.sussex.ac.uk/Users/kroto/">Sussex Fullerene Group</A>  
<LI><A HREF="http://nmr400a.mols.sussex.ac.uk/">The Lawless Group NMR Homepage.</A>
</UL></BASEFONT>
<P>
<H2>Research positions available</H2>
<BASEFONT SIZE="+2">
<P>
</BASEFONT>
