<TITLE>SUMMARY  OF  CURRENT  RESEARCH</TITLE>

<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="MOLS">

<META NAME="CREATIM" CONTENT="1995:6:8:15:48:">

<META NAME="VERSION" CONTENT="1">

</HEAD>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" text="#000000">
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="/images/cpes.gif">   
<H1>Inorganic  and  Organometallic  Chemistry</H1>
</CENTER
<P>
From its inception the School of Chemistry
has been an international centre of excellence in organometallic
chemistry.  The first professor and dean was C Eaborn who continues
to receive research support from SERC and to edit the <I>Journal
of Organometallic Chemistry</I> from his office within the School.
 Professors Lappert, Nixon, and Cloke have made notable contributions
in this area; their research also covers a wide range of related
topics in inorganic chemistry and all elements of the periodic
table.  A common theme is the use of bulky organic groups in alkyls,
alkoxides, amides, or phosphorus compounds to facilitate isolation
of compounds with unusual structures and properties.  Work on
solid state chemistry has been developed by Dr K Prassides.
<P>
<A HREF="/faculty/fgnc/" > Professor F G N Cloke</A>
<P>
Metal vapour syntheses.  Organometallic chemistry, especially
that of the lanthanide elements.
<P>
<A HREF="/faculty/ce/" >Professor C Eaborn</A>
<P>
Organometallic, especially organosilicon, chemistry.
<P>
<A HREF="/faculty/mfl/" >Professor M F Lappert</A>
<P>
Synthetic, structural, and catalytic studies of inorganic compounds.
<P>
<A HREF="/faculty/gal/" >Dr G A Lawless</A>
<P>
Nuclear magnetic resonance spectroscopy, solid state, and solution
studies.
<P>
<A HREF="/faculty/jfn/" >Professor J F Nixon</A>
<P>
Synthetic structural, spectroscopic, and catalytic aspects of inorganic and organometallic
chemistry.  Coordination chemistry of phospha-alkynes.
<P>
<A HREF="/faculty/kp/" >Dr K Prassides</A>
<P>
Mixed valence solids - optical, magnetic, and conducting properties. 
High temperature superconductivity.  Neutron scattering of C60 and C70.
<P>
<A HREF="/faculty/psc/">Dr P Scott</A>
<P>
Organometallic and coordination compounds.  Applications to catalysis.
<P>
<A HREF="/faculty/jds/" >Dr J D Smith</A>
<P> Organometallic chemistry. Chemistry of controlled-release glasses.</P>
<HR><P>
<A HREF="index.html">Return to CPES - Chemistry Home Page </A><P>
<I>Page layout/information:- P. D. Simmons MOLS 3R253
e-mail <A HREF="mailto:p.d.simmons@sussex.ac.uk">kafa9@sussex.ac.uk</A></I></P><P
><I>Page last updated 21st August 1996</I></P>
</BODY>
