<html>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Organic & Medicinal  Chem.</TITLE>
<meta name="resource-type"
value="document">
<meta name="distribution"
value="global">
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" text="#000000">
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="/images/cpes.gif">   
<H3>Organic and Medicinal Chemistry</H3>
</CENTER>
<HR>
Research on complex organic molecules isolated from plants and organisms was initiated 
in the 1960s. The reputation of the School in this area has been built on the research of Professor McCapra on chemi- and bio- luminescence,<A /faculty/dwy/"> Professor D. W. Young</A>
 on the interaction of drugs with target enzymes and<A HREF="/faculty/jrh/">
 Dr. J. R. Hanson</A> on phytochemistry. The stimulating intellectual environment led 
 Professor Sir J. W. Cornforth winner of the Nobel Prize in 1975, to choose to hold his Royal 
Society Professorship within the School. There have also been notable contributions by 
members of the School to physical organic chemistry and the study of reaction mechanisms.
<P>

<H3><A HREF="/faculty/sc/">Dr. S. Caddick</A></H3><P>
Free-radical based synthetic methods. Applications to biologically important heterocycles.
Synthesis of neocarzinostatin.

<H3><A HREF="/faculty/pac/">Dr. P. A. Chaloner</A></H3><P>
Metal-complex-catalysed reactions in organic synthesis. Asymmetric synthesis
Biomedical uses of metal complexes. Materials for non-linear optics.


<H3><A HREF="/faculty/kappa/">Professor Sir John Cornforth</A></H3><P>
Imitation of enzymic catalysis.

<H3><A HREF="/faculty/raj/">Dr. R. A. Jackson</A></H3><P>
Mechanisms of organic, organometallic, biological, and high temperature 
free radical reactions.  Electron spin resonance spectroscopy.

<H3><A HREF="/faculty/jrh/">Dr. J. R. Hanson</A></H3><P>

Plant growth hormones. Chemistry and biosynthesis of terpenoids and steroids.
Fungal metabolites and biotransformations.

<H3><A HREF="/faculty/rt/">Dr. R. Taylor</A></H3><P>
Mechanism of high temperature reactions. Reactivity of novel aromatics
determined using isotopes. Metal-vapour deposition reactions Synthesis and reactions of 
C<SUB>60</SUB> and C<SUB>70</SUB>

<H3><A HREF="/faculty/rmt/">Dr. R. M. Topping</A></H3><P>

The molecular basis of disease. Disease related classification of human blood
Environmental diseases

<H3><A HREF="/faculty/dwy/">Professor D. W. Young</A></H3><P>

Enzymic reactions related to drug action. The chemistry of antibodies
<H3><A HREF="/faculty/drmw/">Dr. D. R. M. Walton</A></H3><P>

Synthetic and mechanistic studies in fullerene chemistry
<P>
<A HREF="/sxres.html">Return to Research Index. 
<IMG SRC="/images/mouse.gif" align="middle"></A>
