<TITLE>PHYSICAL CHEMISTRY & CHEMICAL PHYSICS RESEARCH</TITLE>

<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="MOLS">

<META NAME="CREATIM" CONTENT="1995:6:8:15:48:">

<META NAME="VERSION" CONTENT="1">
<IMG SRC="/images/cpes.gif">   
<H2>Physical  Chemistry  and  Chemical  Physics</H2>

<P>
The first professor of physical chemistry at Sussex was 
<A HREF="/faculty/jnm/"> J. N. Murrell </A> who continues to make important 
contributions in the area of <A HREF="http://tcibm.mols.sussex.ac.uk/tcindex.html" >
 theoretical chemistry </A>.  This has been strengthened by the appointment of
 a full-time lecturer and two research fellows.
  The School's reputation in chemical physics has been built mainly on the
 work of its three professors<A HREF="/faculty/ajmcc/"> A J McCaffery,</A>
 <A HREF="/faculty/hwk/">H W Kroto, </A> and <A HREF="/faculty/ajs/" > A J Stace
</A>.
<P>
<A HREF="/faculty/hwk/" >Professor H W Kroto</A>
<P>
Infrared and microwave spectroscopy.  Interstellar chemistry.
 Gas phase nucleation.  <BR>
C60 and C70.
<P>
<A HREF="/faculty/ajmcc/" >Professor A J McCaffery</A>
<P>
Liquid surface studies using molecular beam techniques.  Molecular
beam spectroscopy.
<P>
<A HREF="/faculty/ajm/" >Dr A J Marks</A>
<P>
Theoretical studies of photoinitiated processes in molecules and
clusters.
<P>
<A HREF="/faculty/jnm/" >Professor J N Murrell</A>
<P>
Theoretical chemistry, valence theory, scattering theory, potential
energy surfaces.
<P>
<A HREF="/faculty/ajs/" >Professor A J Stace</A>
<P>
Cluster spectroscopy and kinetics, molecular beams, mass spectrometry,
and theoretical studies.
<P>
<A HREF="/sxres.html">Return to Sussex research Index.</A><P>
<HR><P><I>Page layout/information:- P. D. Simmons MOLS 3R253
e-mail <A HREF="mailto:p.d.simmons@sussex.ac.uk">kafa9@sussex.ac.uk</A></I></P><P
><I>Page last updated 21th. August 1996</I></P>
</BODY>
