 </CENTER>
<H1 ALIGN=CENTER>Dr Gerard A Lawless</H1><P><B>E-mail <A HREF="mailto:g.a.lawless@sussex.ac.uk">G.A.Lawless@sussex.ac.uk</A></B></P><P>Our <A HREF="http://nmr400a.mols.sussex.ac.uk/">group </A>has two maininterests. The first is the synthesis and characterisation of novel organometallicspecies, particularly those involving low oxidation states or exhibitingcatalytic activity. Our programme concentrates on derivatives of GroupsI, II, IV, XIV, the lanthanides and the actinides. In addition to carbon-basedligands we employ Si-, Sn-, O-, N-, and P-centred groups. Among the catalyticreactions under investigation are olefin polymerisation, hydrosilylation,and methane activation. </P><P>Our second main area of investigation is solid and solution state multinuclearNMR studies of some of the above systems. We are particularly interestedin the observation of hitherto undetected nuclei, e.g. 169Tm, and the useof supercritical fluids as solvents for NMR experiments. Our supercriticalexperiments are carried out in sapphire NMR tubes which permit gases tobe compressed beyond their critical pressure (typically 100 - 200 atm).We have employed supercritical Xe in C-H activation studies, supercriticalCO2 as an alternative &quot;green&quot; solvent for polymerisation reactionsemployed by industry. Many of these projects have associated industrial sponsors. <P>
<IMG SRC="YbI.gif" ALT="Fig. 1" HEIGHT=32 WIDTH=32>
<P>
<HR><B>Selected Publications</B> </P><P>Synthesis and Characterisation of Iodo-functionalised Ytterbium<SUP>II</SUP>and Ytterbium<SUP>III</SUP> Alkoxides. <A HREF="http://chemcomm.clic.ac.uk/cccc9602.htm;internal&sk=03B365CB"><I>J.Chem. Soc., Chem. Commun.</I> 1996, 269.</A></P><P>The First Structurally Authenticated Divalent Lanthanide Siloxide Derivative,[Yb(OSiMe<SUB>2</SUB>Bu<SUP>t</SUP>)(<I>eta</I><SUP>2</SUP>-dme)(<I>u</I><SUP>2</SUP>-OSiMe<SUB>2</SUB>Bu<SUP>t</SUP>)]<SUB>2</SUB><A HREF="http://www.elsevier.com/cas/estoc/contents/SAA/0022328X/SZ961344.html"><I>J.Organomet. Chem.,</I> 1996, <B>506</B>, 293-300</A>.</P><P>The Synthesis and Structure of [Sn{<I>eta</I>-C<SUB>5</SUB>Me<SUB>4</SUB>(SiMe<SUB>2</SUB>Bu<SUP>t</SUP>)}<SUB>2</SUB>]and [Fe{<I>eta</I>-C<SUB>5</SUB>Me<SUB>4</SUB>(SiMe<SUB>2</SUB>Bu<SUP>t</SUP>)}<SUB>2</SUB>].<A HREF="http://chemcomm.clic.ac.uk/cccc9610.htm;internal&sk=03B365CB"><I>J.Chem. Soc., Chem. Commun.</I> 1996, 1101.</A></P><P><SUP>171</SUP>Yb CP MAS NMR Spectroscopy. <A HREF="http://chemcomm.clic.ac.uk/cccc9614.htm;internal&sk=03B365CB"><I>J.Chem. Soc., Chem. Commun.</I> 1996, 1627. </A></P><P>The Synthesis, Characterisation and Molecular Structure of Bis{(<I>tert</I>-butyldimethylsilyl)tetramethylcyclopentadienyl}-Lead.<A HREF="http://pubs.acs.org/journals/orgnd7/"><I>Organometallics,</I>1996, <B>15</B>, 3905.</A></P><P>The Synthesis, Structure and Reactivity of [Yb(<I>eta</I>-C<SUB>5</SUB>Me<SUB>5</SUB>){Si(SiMe<SUB>3</SUB>)<SUB>3</SUB>}(thf)<SUB>2</SUB>]<A HREF="http://chemcomm.clic.ac.uk/cccc9620.htm;internal&sk=000573DE"><I>J.Chem. Soc., Chem. Commun.,</I> 1996, 2323.</A> </P><P>The Synthesis, Structure and Reactivity of Ionogenic [Sn(<I>eta</I>-Cp<SUP>R</SUP>)Cl]Derivatives. <I><A HREF="http://chemcomm.clic.ac.uk/cccc9620.htm;internal&sk=000573DE">J.Chem. Soc., Chem.,Commun., </A></I><A HREF="http://chemcomm.clic.ac.uk/cccc9620.htm;internal&sk=000573DE">1996,2337.</A><HR></P></BODY></HTML>
