<HTML>
<TITLE>Professor John  F. Nixon</TITLE>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" text="#000000">
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC=/images/cpes.gif>
<H1>Professor John  F. Nixon</H1>
</CENTER>
<HR><P>
e-mail:- <A HREF="mailto:j.nixon@sussex.ac.uk">J.Nixon@sussex.ac.uk</A>

<P>
Current activity centres around synthetic, structural, and spectroscopic studies of novel phosphorus
compounds and their ligating behaviour towards transition metals.

In recent years it has become apparent that phosphorus has an exceptional ability to mimic the
chemistry of carbon. It is now possible to synthesise stable phosphorus analogues of the better
known unsaturated hydrocarbon 7r-complexes which have been responsible for the rapid
development of organotransition metal chemistry and its importance in homogeneous catalysis.
The ligating properties of compounds containing phosphorus-carbon multiple bonds were examined
for the first time at Sussex and now a wide variety of complexes have been synthesised and
structurally characterised. A recent extension has led to the first examples of 11 l-ligated XP=NR
and [P-NR]+ systems and the syntheses of novel 'cage' compounds such as As4C4But4 and
P6C6But6. These compounds may have importance both in catalysis and as precursors for a
variety of new materials.
<P>
<IMG SRC="jfn.gif" ALT="Sorry you cannot display this">
<P>
<STRONG>Selected Publications</STRONG>
<P>
Reviews: Chem. Revs., 1988, 88, 1327; Endeavour, 1991,<STRONG> 15</STRONG>, 49; Chem. Ind., 1993, 404.
First structural characterisation of penta- and hexa-phosphorus analogues of ferrocene. Synthesis,
crystal, and molecular structure of the air stable, sublimable iron sandwich compounds
[Fe(T15-c2R2P3)2] and [Fe(T15-c3R3P2)(rl5-c2R2p3)]~ (R = But),<CITE> J. Chem. Soc., Chem.
Commun.,</CITE> 1987, 1946.
<P>
Use of 1,3 diphosphacyclobutadiene complexes in the synthesis of mixed metal aggregates
containing cobalt, rhodium and platinum. Crystal and molecular structure of the remarkable hexa-
rhodium complex [Rh2C12{Rh(rl5-C~H~)(P2C2But2)}4], <CITE>Heteroatom Chem.,</CITE> 1991, <STRONG>2</STRONG>, 253.
<P>
An n2 transition state for the insertion of [Pd(dppe)] fragments into the phosphorus-carbon bonds
of phosphiranepentacarbonyltungsten complexes. Crystal and molecular structures of
(Z)-[W(CO)sPPhCHPhCHPh], [2(R)* 3(S)*,4(R)*]-(+)- and [2(R)* 3(S)*,4(R)*]-(+)-
[Pd(dppe)(CHPhCHPhPPh)W(CO)s], dppe = 1,2-bis(diphenylphosphino)ethane, <CITE>J. Chem. Soc.,
Dalton Trans., </CITE>1993, 1811.
<P>
Synthesis and characterisation of a novel arsa-alkyne tetramer and its reaction with [Fe2(CO)g].
Crystal and molecular structures of As4C4But4 and As4C4But4Fe(CO)4, <CITE>Angew. Chem., Int.
Edn. Engl.</CITE>, 1993, <STRONG>32</STRONG>, 103.
