<html>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Dr. K. Prassides</TITLE>
<meta name="resource-type"
value="document">
<meta name="distribution"
value="global">
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" text="#000000">
<CENTER>
<img src="/images/cpes.gif"></CENTER>
<HR>
E-Mail:<A HREF="mailto:k.prassides@sussex.ac.uk">K. Prassides@sussex.ac.uk</A><P>
We are interested in a varied range of structural, magnetic and dynamic
problems in modern materials, straddling the areas of solid state inorganic 
chemistry and chemical physics. Our synthetic programme is complemented by a 
range of experimental techniques encompassing X-ray and neutron scattering, 
muon spectroscopy and conductivity and susceptibility measurements.
<P>
Current areas if interest include:
<UL>
<LI> The solid state chemistry of pristine fullerines and their novel 
derivatives, with emphasis on superconducting fullerides.
<LI> The solid state chemistry of transition and post-transition metal 
oxides and in particular their novel conducting and magnetic properties 
including superconductivity and spin-glass behaviour.
<LI>The inercalation of chemistry of layered inorganic hosts. The guest  
species encompass a variety of inorganic and organic molecules including 
conductive polymers.
<LI>Theoretical vibronic studies of multinulear mixed valency systems 
including clusters, linear chains and planar networks.
</UL>
<P>
The group makes extensive use of international synchrotron, neutron and 
muon facilities (ISI and Daresbury, U.K., Institut Laue Langevin, Grenoble, 
France, Paul Scherrer Institute, Zurich, Switzerland, National Institute of 
Standards and Technology, Gaithersburg, USA)
<P>
<STRONG>Selected Publications</STRONG><P>
Crystal structure and bonding of ordered C<SUB>60</SUB>, 
<CITE> Nature,</CITE> 1991, <STRONG>353,</STRONG>147
<P>
Vibrational spectroscopy of superconducting K<SUB>3</SUB>C<SUB>60</SUB>,
<CITE> Nature,</CITE> 1991, <STRONG>354,</STRONG>462.
Mu@64C<SUB>70</SUB>: monitoring the dynamics of fullerenes from inside the cage
<CITE> J. Phys. Chem.,</CITE> 1992, <STRONG>96,</STRONG>10 600.
<P>
Sr<SUB>2-x</SUB>Ba<SUB>x</SUB>CuO<SUB>2</SUB>(CO<SUB>3</SUB>): a series of antiferromagnetic layered oxide carbonates,
<CITE> Inorg. Chem.,</CITE> 1993, <STRONG>32,</STRONG>383.
<P>
Exchange and vibronic interactions in a tetrahedral, five-electron mixed-valence cluster,
<CITE> J. Chem. Phys..,</CITE> 1993, <STRONG>98,</STRONG>4805.
<hr>
