   <TITLE>The Chemistry Job Hunters Guide.</TITLE>
   <META NAME="Author" CONTENT="Douglas M. Barr">
   <META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Mozilla/3.0b8Gold (Win16; I) [Netscape]">
   <META NAME="Description" CONTENT="A link site to Chemistry related jobs on the Internet.">
   <META NAME="KeyWords" CONTENT="chemistry, chemical, job, career, employment, douglas, barr, internet">
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="pebldash.gif">

<CENTER><P><IMG SRC="logo.gif" BORDER=1 HEIGHT=100 WIDTH=100></P></CENTER>

<CENTER><P><B><FONT COLOR="#0000FF"><FONT SIZE=+3>The Chemistry Job Hunters
Guide.</FONT></FONT></B></P></CENTER>

<CENTER><P><I><FONT SIZE=+1>Page created and maintained by <A HREF="dmbhome1.html">Doug
Barr</A>.</FONT></I></P></CENTER>

<CENTER><P><I><FONT SIZE=+1>You are visitor number <IMG SRC="counter.gif" HEIGHT=20 WIDTH=120>&nbsp;&nbsp;to
visit this site. </FONT></I></P></CENTER>

<CENTER><P><I><FONT SIZE=+1>Hmm....remind me to E-mail Webcounter.</FONT></I></P></CENTER>

<CENTER><P><IMG SRC="colorbar.gif" HEIGHT=1 WIDTH=600></P></CENTER>

<UL>
<P><B><FONT SIZE=+1>It was as I entered the dark twilight at the end of
the second year of my Chemistry D.Phil. (at the lovely University of Sussex)
that I realised what a pain in the bum it was to try and find a job. Hence
this page. </FONT></B></P>
</UL>

<UL>
<P><B><FONT SIZE=+1>No longer will you have to trawl around your Careers
Service to find empty folders; now you can sit in the comfort of your own
lab/home/toilet, surf round the World to a major chemical manufacturer
to be greeted with those cheery words;</FONT></B></P>

<CENTER><P><B><FONT SIZE=+3>404 Not Found</FONT></B></P></CENTER>

<P><FONT SIZE=+1><B>One thing: the only stuff you'll find here is on those
Companies which are forward looking enough to have WWW sites </B>(<I>!!??-
Ed.)</I><B> If you visit any of these sites and have any thoughts, comments,
questions about them, </B></FONT><B><I><FONT SIZE=+3>PLEASE PLEASE PLEASE
</FONT></I><FONT SIZE=+1>contact the Webmaster (or whoever) and let them
know. The reason I'm so keen for you to do this is simple. Companies need
to see that their Web sites are worth maintaining. As a job hunter, you'll
quickly appreciate the value of such sites. Let's try to ensure that they
stay there. </FONT></B><FONT SIZE=+1>(<I>Enough preaching; get on with
it- Ed</I>)<B>.</B></FONT></P>

<CENTER><P><B><FONT SIZE=+1>Okay, I've divided the information into two
pages; </FONT></B></P></CENTER>

<CENTER><P><B><FONT SIZE=+1>if you're looking for employment with a specific
company, have a look at the <A HREF="chemcomp.html">Companies Page</A>.
</FONT></B></P></CENTER>

<CENTER><P><B><FONT SIZE=+1>If you're just in the market (<I>ie. desperate
enough to work for anyone</I>) keep reading....</FONT></B></P></CENTER>

<CENTER><P><IMG SRC="colorbar.gif" HEIGHT=1 WIDTH=600></P></CENTER>

<CENTER><P><B><I><FONT SIZE=+3>The Premier League.</FONT></I></B></P></CENTER>

<UL>
<CENTER><P><B><FONT SIZE=+1>These are the cream of Chemistry jobs. You
<I>must</I> visit all these sites.</FONT></B></P></CENTER>
</UL>

<P><FONT SIZE=+1>The first is <B><I>Chemistry &amp; Industry's</I> </B>excellent<B>
</B>Job Page. (Find it <A HREF="http://ci.mond.org/jobs/jobsearch.html">here</A>).
They can also E-mail any job vacancies directly to you for free. (Do that
<A HREF="http://ci.mond.org/jobs/jobregister.html">here</A>).</FONT></P>

<P><FONT SIZE=+1>Next, try <B><I>Chemistry Today's</I></B> closely related
Jobsearch facility (Find it <A HREF="http://chemistry.mond.org/jobsearch.html">here</A>).
They too can <A HREF="http://chemistry.mond.org/jobregister.html">E-mail
jobs</A> to you.</FONT></P>

<P><FONT SIZE=+1>The <B><I><A HREF="http://chemistry.rsc.org/rsc/jobs3.htm">Royal
Society of Chemistry</A></I></B> usually has <B><I>hundreds</I></B> of
jobs and post-Docs on offer.</FONT></P>

<P><FONT SIZE=+1>The <B><I><A HREF="http://ecs.tu-bs.de/ECS-WWW/neu/special/Jobcenter.html">European
Chemical Society</A></I></B> is also worth a look. Either for <A HREF="http://ecs.tu-bs.de/ECS-WWW/neu/Special/Com.html">jobs</A>
or <A HREF="http://ecs.tu-bs.de/ECS-WWW/neu/Special/Doc.html">post-Docs</A>.</FONT></P>

<P><FONT SIZE=+1><B><I><A HREF="http://www.nature.com/Nature2/serve?SID=29501507&CAT=Classified&PG=Jobs/jobshome.html">Nature</A></I></B>
claims to have 'the most comprehensive international listing of jobs (<I>and
post-Docs</I>) on the Internet'. Updated weekly no less(!).<I> <B><A HREF="http://recruit.sciencemag.org/science/feature/classified/search.shtml">Science</A></B></I>
is pretty good too. (<I>Both of these are best used before about 1pm. GMT</I>).</FONT></P>

<P><FONT SIZE=+1>Margaret Riley maintains an excellent site on job hunting
the Internet; <A HREF="http://www.jobtrak.com/jobguide/">The Riley Guide,</A>
which is worth a look. (<I><A HREF="http://www.jobtrak.com/jobguide/mfriley.html">Margaret</A>'s
worth a look too!- Ed.</I>)</FONT></P>

<P><FONT SIZE=+1>Finally, If you know how to trawl newsgroups for gems,
you should try out <A HREF="news:sci.research.careers">sci.research.careers</A>,
<A HREF="news:sci.research.postdoc">sci.research.postdoc</A>, <A HREF="news:misc.jobs.fields.chemistry">misc.jobs.fields.chemistry</A>
or even <A HREF="news:uk.jobs">uk.jobs</A> (this last one is only if you've
decided to give up chemistry for goat-herding). A fairly exhaustive list
of chemistry related newsgroups can be found at <A HREF="http://www.chem.ucla.edu/chem_news.html">UCLA</A>.</FONT></P>

<CENTER><P><IMG SRC="colorbar.gif" HEIGHT=1 WIDTH=600></P></CENTER>

<CENTER><P><B><I><FONT SIZE=+3>The First Division.</FONT></I></B></P></CENTER>

<CENTER><P><B><FONT SIZE=+1>These are the big Websearchers. Although not
specific to Chemistry, you can usually pull out a few nuggets, albeit with
a bit of lateral thinking!</FONT></B></P></CENTER>

<P><FONT SIZE=+1>How about <A HREF="http://a2z.lycos.com/Science_and_Technology/Chemistry/">Lycos</A>?
Particularly their <A HREF="http://a2z.lycos.com/Science_and_Technology/Chemistry/Companies/">Companies</A>
page.</FONT></P>

<P><FONT SIZE=+1>Not into Lycos? How about <A HREF="http://webcrawler.com/select/bus.employment.html">Webcrawler</A>?</FONT></P>

<P><FONT SIZE=+1>Or even good old <A HREF="http://www.yahoo.com/Science/Chemistry/">Yahoo</A>!</FONT></P>

<P><FONT SIZE=+1>Ever visited the <A HREF="http://www.jobweb.org/catapult/">Jobweb
catapult</A>?</FONT></P>

<P><FONT SIZE=+1>Hmm...having to work a bit now. Aren't we.....? There's
always <A HREF="http://guide-p.infoseek.com/Titles?qt=employment+chem&col=WW&sv=N2&Seek+Now.x=18&Seek+Now.y=10">infoseek</A>
(don't hold your breath though. This site can be verrryyyyy sloooooooowwwwwwwww...............).</FONT></P>

<CENTER><P><IMG SRC="colorbar.gif" HEIGHT=1 WIDTH=600></P></CENTER>

<CENTER><P><B><I><FONT SIZE=+3>Beezer Homes Sunday League.</FONT></I></B></P></CENTER>

<CENTER><P><B><FONT SIZE=+1>Now things start to get a little less optimistic.
These guys usually require you to be (a) American, and (b) an expert in
computer linguistics. The latter is needed to figure out how to use their
generally appalling interfaces. Anyway, if you've got nothing better to
do, and the University is footing the bill.........</FONT></B></P></CENTER>

<CENTER><P><FONT SIZE=+1><A HREF="http://www.careermosaic-uk.co.uk/">Career
Mosaic </A>(UK site) 2. <A HREF="http://www1.monster.com:80/home/firstime.htm">Monster
Board</A> 0. (Slow. Monster bored?)</FONT></P></CENTER>

<CENTER><P><FONT SIZE=+1><A HREF="http://www.careersite.com/cgi/search_jobs">Career
site</A> 1. <A HREF="http://heme.gsu.edu/post_docs/koen/wjobs.html">Koen
van Aken</A> 3.</FONT></P></CENTER>

<CENTER><P><FONT SIZE=+1><A HREF="http://www.belganet.be/~belganet/jobs/jobs.htm">Euro-Jobs</A>
1 (just for the name). <A HREF="http://www.anu.edu.au/psychology/Academia/chem.htm">Academia</A>
2. (academic jobs only. Limited.).</FONT></P></CENTER>

<CENTER><P><FONT SIZE=+1><A HREF="http://hackberry.chem.niu.edu:70/1/ChemJob">Chemistry
Clearing House </A>1. <A HREF="http://chemscope.com/cgi-win/posit.exe">Chemscope</A>
1.</FONT></P></CENTER>

<CENTER><P><IMG SRC="colorbar.gif" HEIGHT=1 WIDTH=600></P></CENTER>

<CENTER><P><A HREF="mailto:d.m.barr@susx.ac.uk"><IMG SRC="mailbox.gif" BORDER=0 HEIGHT=94 WIDTH=94 ALIGN=CENTER></A><A HREF="mailto:d.m.barr@susx.ac.uk">Please
E-mail me with any comments or suggestions.</A></P></CENTER>

<CENTER><P><A HREF="sjcgrp01.html"><IMG SRC="handleft.gif" BORDER=0 HEIGHT=14 WIDTH=33 ALIGN=CENTER></A><A HREF="http://www.mols.susx.ac.uk./mols/resgrps/sjc/sjcgrp01.html">Back
to the Caddick Group Homepage</A> &nbsp;or <A HREF="chemcomp.html">on to
the Companies page.</A><A HREF="chemcomp.html"><IMG SRC="handrite.gif" BORDER=0 HEIGHT=14 WIDTH=33></A></P></CENTER>
</UL>

</BODY>
