<html>
<head>
   <title>Steven Bromfield Homepage</title>
   <meta name="Author" content="Douglas M. Barr">
   <meta name="GENERATOR" content="Mozilla/3.0b4Gold (Win16)">
   <meta name="KeyWords" content="microwave, ego, welsh, synthesis, organic, asymmetric">
</head>
<body text="#FFFFFFFF" bgcolor="#FFFFFFFF" link="#FFFFFF00" vlink="#000080" alink="#FFFFFF00" background="wales2.gif">

<center><p><b><font COLOR="#FFFFFF00"><font SIZE=+4>Steven's Homepage</font></font></b></p></center>

<center><p><img src="steveb.jpg" border=0 height=256 width=199></p></center>

<p><b><font COLOR="#FFFFFFFF"><font SIZE=+1>HOWDY FOLKS, STEVIE B HERE
TO TELL YOU A LITTLE SOMETHING ABOUT MYSELF. </font></font></b></p>

<p><b><i><font COLOR="#FFFFFFFF"><font SIZE=+1>THE CADDICK GROUP IS VERY
LUCKY TO HAVE ME, AS I'M SURE THE REST OF THE GROUP WILL AGREE. FROM THE
DAY I ARRIVED, THE LAB HAS BEEN A HAPPY SMILEY PLACE TO WORK, AND I KNOW
MY WITTY COMMENTS AND INTELLECTUAL OPINIONS ARE WELL RECIEVED BY THE GROUP
AS A WHOLE.</font></font></i></b></p>

<p><b><i><font COLOR="#FFFFFFFF"><font SIZE=+1>YES I MUST ADMIT THAT I
AM PROBABLY THE BEST CHEMIST IN THE LAB. IT MUST COME FROM BEING WELSH!!!!!.</font></font></i></b></p>

<p><b><font COLOR="#FFFFFFFF"><font SIZE=+1>NOW TO THE SERIOUS STUFF.</font></font></b></p>

<p><b><font COLOR="#FFFFFFFF"><font SIZE=+1>MY WORK INVOLVES MICROWAVE
ASSISTED ORGANIC TRANSFORMATIONS.</font></font></b></p>

<p><b><font COLOR="#FFFFFFFF"><font SIZE=+1>It has been known for many
years that an insulating material can be heated by the application of a
high frequency electromagnetic wave. Organic chemistry is an area to which
microwaves have been found to be beneficial, in that they have been found
to increase the rate of reaction times and in many cases also increase
the yield of the reactions. The purpose of this project is to investigate
the effect of microwave radiation on a range of free radical based transformations,
with regards to the effect on the efficiency of a range of stereoselective
free radical reactions and also on the effect of tin mediated inter and
intra radical reactions. The first objection of the project, however, was
to examine the Baylis-Hillman reaction to see what effect microwave irradiation
would have on itís reaction rate and yield. The control of relative stereochemistry
in organic reactions is very important. The second objective of the project
was to use the microwave oven to attempt to control the stereochemistry
in the radical mediated allylation reaction of phenyl-2-bromo-3-methoxybutyrate
formed from the methoxybromination of methyl-trans-cinnamate. </font></font></b></p>

<center><p><img src="stevmek1.gif" border=0 height=245 width=720></p></center>

<p><b><font COLOR="#FFFFFFFF"><font SIZE=+1>The third part of the project
is to use NaI, Fe, Fe(II) or Fe(III) to initiate the following radical
reaction instead of tin compounds (eg. hexabuyltditin) or AIBN which are
toxic compounds. </font></font></b></p>

<center><p><img src="stevmek2.gif" border=2 height=209 width=721></p></center>

<center><p><font COLOR="#000080"><font SIZE=+2><a href="/resgrps/sjc/welcome.html">Back
to the Caddick Group Homepage.</a></font></font></p></center>

<center><p><i><font COLOR="#000080">Copyright Douglas Barr 30/6/96.</font></i></p></center>

