<HR>

<A NAME="Peter"></A><H1>Peter</H1>
<TABLE>
<TR>
  <TD VALIGN=TOP width="15%"><BIG>Totem Animal:</BIG><BR>Lion</TD><TD width="20%"></TD>
 <TD VALIGN=TOP width="15%"><BIG>Star Sign:</BIG><BR>Cornucopia</TD>
 <TD VALIGN=TOP width="20%"><BIG>Loves:</BIG><BR>My mum<BR>Weetbix<BR>Flying<BR>Music<BR><A HREF="/spis/softserv.htm#Programming">Delphi</A><BR></TD>
 <TD VALIGN=TOP width="20%"><BIG>Loathes:</BIG><BR>99% of New Zealand television<BR>Christchurch Drivers<BR><A HREF="http://www.greenpeace.org/~comms/rw/pkcant.html">Jacques Chirac</A></TD>
 <TD VALIGN=TOP  width="30%"><BIG>Fondest wish:</BIG><BR>My very own Rutan (it's an aeroplane...<BR>but not just any aeroplane)</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<H3>Qualifications & Experience:</H3>
<UL>
<LI>Private Pilot's License (please send money)</LI>
<LI>BTech (Hons) (Industrial Engineering)</LI>
<LI>Once I got given a bunch of trophies at school, but I had to give them back.</LI>
</UL>

<P>In the mid-80s, I spent six inscrutable years in Japan working for a great little computer company which later got swallowed by a giant (Toshiba). Some of my time was spent refereeing a development team consisting of stroppy Kiwis, Irish, Nihonjin, Koreans and one token American. When I wasn't doing that, I was jet-setting all over the world, learning interesting things about the insides of hotels, airports and restaurants.

<P>In '89 <A HREF="/spis/people.htm#Vicki">Vicki</A> and I spent a few fantastic months re-visiting these places, and discovered that they had museums, architecture, scenery and <EM>people!</EM> Then we came home and settled in Christchurch, New Zealand, which is <A HREF="http://WWW.Regy.Canterbury.ac.nz/CH_Promo/HasItAll.html">The Place To Be</A>.

<P>And started <A HREF="/spis/pin.htm#SPIS">this business...</A>

<A NAME="SAT"><H3>What I do with my time:</H3></A>
<P>When working, I <A HREF="/spis/softserv.htm#SoftwareEngineering">design and develop software</A>, generally Windows-based applications these days. Most of this is done using <A HREF="/spis/softserv.htm#Programming">Borland's Delphi and Paradox</A>. At the moment, I'm up to my neck in <A HREF="/spis/softserv.htm">electronic publishing</A> applications, such as presenting databases <A HREF="/spis/softserv.htm#WebPage">on the Web</A>.  I really <I>enjoy</I> this stuff!

<P>Otherwise, I fly whenever the bank balance is almost in the black, travel whenever I can't get away with flying, dress up in funny clothes and pose as a <A HREF="/spis/sca.htm">12th-Century</A> scoundrel, and read endless books to David and Perry. That is, when we're not up on the roof playing petanque.

<P>I write stories too, at least one of which was described as "amusing". It even got published: in <A HREF="http://www.vuw.ac.nz/~thetroll/phlogiston.html"><CITE>Phlogiston.</CITE></A><BR><A HREF="/spis/autotran.htm">I've got proof!</A>

<P>I've also been known to act, but I won't bore you with the reviews...

<P><IMG SRC="/spis/images/letters.gif"><A HREF="mailto:peter@spis.co.nz"> Mail Peter</A> (be gentle).
<P>

<HR>

<A NAME="Vicki"></A><H1>Vicki</H1>
<TABLE>
<TR>
  <TD VALIGN=TOP width="15%"><BIG>Totem Animal:</BIG><BR>Ferret, or maybe a Dragon, or a White Boar, no, a...</TD><TD width="20%"></TD>
 <TD VALIGN=TOP width="15%"><BIG>Star Sign:</BIG><BR>Asparagus<TD>
 <TD VALIGN=TOP width="20%"><BIG>Loves:</BIG><BR>Ferrets<BR>Dark summer night skies<BR><A HREF="http://www.ozemail.com.au/~dcundy/harps/harp1.html">
Harps</A><BR>Science<BR></TD>
 <TD VALIGN=TOP width="20%"><BIG>Loathes:</BIG><BR>Getting up before 8am<BR>Upstart Tudors<BR><A HREF="http://www.greenpeace.org/~comms/rw/pkcant.html">Jacques Chirac</A></TD>
 <TD width="30%"><BIG>Fondest wish:</BIG><BR>To find a knight patron for my <A HREF="/spis/sca.htm">medi&aelig;val</A> archery company</TD>
<TR>
</TABLE>

<H3>Qualifications & Experience:</H3>
<UL>
<LI>BSc (Psychology) BA (Sociology)  </LI>
<LI>Mother of two horribly cute little boys (must be genetics)</LI>
<LI>I've got a big bronze Science and Technology Medal of New Zealand which makes a great paperweight</LI>
</UL>

<P>After abandoning Auckland to start a Canterbury science degree in astrophysics, I wandered through a startlingly diverse range of departments in search of a major, and ended up with the perfect academic background for a science journalist -- I know a little about everything, but not a great deal about anything in particular.

<P>I spent my sojourn in Japan working for a <A HREF="http://www.twics.com/~COMLINE/links.html">
science and technology</A> database and, later, as a science and front-page editor for one of the four main English daily newspapers, <A HREF="http://www.yomiuri.co.jp/index-e.htm"><CITE>The Daily Yomiuri.</CITE></A> I also ended up as local correspondent for about a dozen technical magazines, covering broadcasting, telecommunications, energy, ceramics, even shipping and the duty-free industry.

<P>Frustration at the lack of science coverage in the New Zealand media led me to establish the <A HREF="/spis/nzsm/nzsm.htm"><I>New Zealand Science Monthly</I></A> in 1990. While it hasn't exactly led to fame and fortune, we must be doing something right -- we're still going strong!


<H3>What I do with my time:</H3>

<P>Well, there's the <A HREF="/spis/nzsm/nzsm.htm"><I>New Zealand Science Monthly</I></A> and the other regular (and irregular) <A HREF="/spis/editserv.htm">publishing</A> work that I either do or manage as SPIS's managing editor. (If you want to be seen to support New Zealand science and technology, and have dollars to burn in your advertising budget, I want to <A HREF="mailto:nzsm@spis.co.nz">hear from you!)</A>

<P>Then there's being Chair-entity for the <A HREF="/spis/skeptics.htm">New Zealand Skeptics</A>, which involves (among other things) early morning calls from radio stations every Friday 13th. *sigh*

<P>If I'm lucky, I get to put on my 16-gauge steel helm and camail, my breastplate, my padded gambeson, my knee and elbow pads, my groin protection, my puncture-proof trousers and my boots, and go out and shoot arrows at <A HREF="/spis/people.htm#Peter">Peter</A> (see <A HREF="/spis/sca.htm">SCA</A>).

<P>If I'm <I>really</I> lucky, I hit him.

<P><IMG SRC="/spis/images/letters.gif"><A HREF="mailto:nzsm@spis.co.nz"> Mail Vicki</A> -- she doesn't bite. Honest.
<BR>
<HR>

<A NAME="Phil"></A>

<H1>Phil</H1>

<TABLE>
   <TR>
      <TD VALIGN=TOP width="20%"><BIG>Totem Animal:</BIG><BR>Sloth</TD>
      <TD VALIGN=TOP width="15%"><BIG>Star Sign:</BIG><BR><IMG SRC="/spis/images/pentacle.gif" alt="Pentacle"></TD>
      <TD VALIGN=TOP width="20%"><BIG>Likes:</BIG><BR>Sleep<BR>Toys<BR>Ouzo<BR></TD>
      <TD VALIGN=TOP width="20%"><BIG>Loathes:</BIG><BR>Idiots<BR>Illiteracy<BR>Legumes</TD>
      <TD VALIGN=TOP width="25%"><BIG>Fondest wish:</BIG><BR>Arbitrarily great wealth</TD>
   <TR>
   </TABLE>

<H3>Qualifications & Experience:</H3>

<UL>
   <LI>BSc (Computer Science) BA (Psychology)</LI>
   <LI>I can do many things -- and around here I usually have to</LI>
   </UL>

<P>
After a decade or so as a university student and part-time tutor, I sort of drifted bit by bit into a job with this place. Not as much fun, but the money's a bit better and I still don't have to have a haircut or wear shoes.

<H3>What I do with my time:</H3>

<P>Aside from slaving at work, I sleep, read, argue, listen to music, procrastinate, play games... you know, sort of like everyone else really. Some day I may get around to updating this page and doing a comprehensive sloth page.

<P><IMG SRC="/spis/images/letters.gif">
<A HREF="mailto:hairy@sloth.southern.co.nz">Mail Phil.</A>

