<A NAME="Fitz"></A><H1>Peter Fitzpatrick (Fitz)</H1>
<TABLE>
<TR>
  <TD VALIGN=TOP width="15%"><BIG>Totem Animal:</BIG><BR>Elephant</TD><TD width="20%"></TD>
 <TD VALIGN=TOP width="15%"><BIG>Star Sign:</BIG><BR>Emma Thompson<TD>
 <TD VALIGN=TOP width="20%"><BIG>Loves:</BIG><BR>Aikido<BR>Fresh clean drawing paper<BR><A HREF="http://www.lfbs.rwth-aachen.de/~markolf/Moto_Links.html">Powerful motorcycles</A><BR></TD>
 <TD VALIGN=TOP width="20%"><BIG>Loathes:</BIG><BR>Getting out of bed<BR>Silverbeet<BR><A HREF="http://www.greenpeace.org/~comms/rw/pkcant.html">Jacques Chirac</A></TD>
 <TD VALIGN=TOP width="30%"><BIG>Fondest wish:</BIG><BR>To become phenomenally wealthy and live a life of sybaritic luxury without ever having to work for it</TD>
<TR>
</TABLE>

<H3>Qualifications & Experience:</H3>
<UL>
<LI>North Island small-bore champion 1977</LI>
<LI>Fieldcraft badge (Scouts)</LI>
</UL>

<P>I provide the graphic design side of things for SPIS when they are feeling artistically challenged. I've worked with them designing <A HREF="/spis/editserv.htm">covers for publications,</A> graphics for international marketing campaigns and book illustrations for their Japanese corporate clients.

<H3>What I do with my time:</H3>

<P>I take people's money away for entertainment beyond their wildest dreams. When I'm not officially working,  I play with my computer a lot trying to find yet more bugs in <A HREF="http://brother.cc.monash.edu.au/alst4/csc3170/nbai1/WWW/corel.html">CorelDraw</A> and <A HREF="http://macwww.db.erau.edu/www_virtual_lib/aviation/flightsim.html">flight simulators.</A>

<P>When I'm <I>really</I> stuck for something to do, I spend five minutes or so adding something new to The Mural, at <A HREF="/spis/people.htm#Peter">Peter</A> and <A HREF="/spis/people.htm#Vicki">Vicki's</A> house.

<P><IMG SRC="/spis/images/letters.gif"> I am temporarily between email addresses so you'll just have to email <A HREF="mailto:nzsm@spis.co.nz">Vicki.</A>

<HR>

<A NAME="Nick"></A><H1>Nick Kim</H1>
<TABLE>
<TR>
  <TD VALIGN=TOP width="15%"><BIG>Totem Animal:</BIG><BR>Martin Honeysett</TD><TD width="20%"></TD>
 <TD VALIGN=TOP width="15%"><BIG>Star Sign:</BIG><BR>Nemesis, the mysterious tenth planet<TD>
 <TD VALIGN=TOP width="20%"><BIG>Loves:</BIG><BR>Coffee (caffeine), chocolate (theobromine) and their marvellous mind-enhancing effects<BR></TD>
 <TD VALIGN=TOP width="20%"><BIG>Loathes:</BIG><BR>Beetroot and many other vegetables of questionable lineage<BR><A HREF="http://www.greenpeace.org/~comms/rw/pkcant.html">Jacques Chirac</A></TD>
 <TD VALIGN=TOP width="30%"><BIG>Fondest wish:</BIG><BR> Wants to synthesize a molecule which combines the two wonder alkaloids and essential nutrients, caffeine and theobromine, to provide the ultimate perk-you-up sugar rush.</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<H3>Qualifications & Experience:</H3>
<UL>
<LI>Nice temperament</LI>
<LI>Good with children and dogs</LI>
<LI>Plays the guitar really badly</LI>
<LI> I did a degree, and then did some more.  Nobody tried to stop me. Heh heh heh.</LI>
</UL>

<P>Some say I only lecture at Waikato's Chemistry department in order to support  my cartooning habit.  However, chocolate and coffee can also be expensive.

<H3>What I do with my time:</H3>

<P>Forge obscure Salvadore Dali paintings, like the hitherto unknown work <A HREF="/spis/images/12goats.gif"><CITE>The Persistence of Goats</CITE></A> (148K).

<P>Draw <STRONG>NICK</STRONG> cartoons, inspired mainly by caffeine and theobromine. They are created in a secret home laboratory in the dead of night.

<P>Once born, they discard the host and assume lives of their own, migrating inexorably outward from the point of their birth to seek out potential publishing grounds (such as the <A HREF="/spis/nzsm/nzsm.htm"><CITE>New Zealand Science Monthly.</CITE></A>) I haven't yet observed it, but I suspect that once these things are in your brain, they will begin to replicate, consuming your cognitive juices in their relentless progression to the next horrible stage of their parasitic life-cycle. Like <A HREF="/spis/images/photon.gif">this one</A> (14K).

<P align=center>As if this wasn't enough, <STRONG>NICK</STRONG> cartoons also have a second life as<BR>
<A HREF="http://galadriel.ecaetc.ohio-state.edu/tc/sm/"><IMG vspace=5 SRC="/spis/images/smlogo.gif" alt="Strange Matter"></A><BR> a complete, online <A HREF="http://galadriel.ecaetc.ohio-state.edu/tc/sm/">archive</A> of every image which escaped his pen.<BR>You have been warned...

<P><IMG SRC="/spis/images/letters.gif"><A HREF="mailto:ndkim@waikato.ac.nz"> Mail Nick.</A> Now roll over. <STRONG>Good</STRONG> dog.

<P>

