         <H2><BR>
         Planned French Radiation Tryst Banned
        </H2>
        <H3>
        Diplomat Under Mushroom Cloud
        </H3>
         <P ALIGN=CENTER><I>WEB -- November 20</I>

        <P><STRONG>Radioactive French Ambassador Jacques Le Blanc is persona non grata at New Zealand's National Radiation
        Laboratory, banned from his t&ecirc;te-&agrave;-t&ecirc;te with lab head Dr Andrew McEwan on the orders of Minister of Health
        Jenny Shipley.</STRONG>
         </TD>

      <TD ALIGN=CENTER COLSPAN=2>
         <IMG SRC="/spis/images/sm141.gif" ALT="Cartoon (8K)" HEIGHT=500 WIDTH=340 BORDER=1><BR>
         Super-dense proto-politicians, by <A HREF="/spis/people.htm#Nick">Nick</A><P>
         </TD>
      </TR>

   <TR>
      <TD COLSPAN=5>
         <P><BIG>T</BIG>he fear of "le contamination nucleaire" could well spread to other sites, warns one source. "We'll have to ban M. Le Blanc from New Zealand hospitals that use radiotherapy, from universities that offer physics degrees, from manufacturers of smoke detectors -- from any other place where he might try to persuade us that radioactivity has its uses."
<P>Officials were reportedly concerned that scientific evidence might get in the way of politically appropriate action, and warned that a dangerous precedent might be set were important information to be taken out of the control of the political sphere.
         </TD>
      </TR>
      </TABLE>
    </TD>
    </TR> <!-- End of row 3 -->

<TR> <!-- Row 4, Stop Press -->
   <TD COLSPAN=6>     <TABLE WIDTH=715 BORDER=2 >
   <TR>
      <TD COLSPAN=3>
         <BLINK><STRONG>STOP PRESS:</STRONG></BLINK>
Queen banned from talking to Bolger children -- fears of Republican discussion! Lockwood Smith banned from Vice-Chancellors' meeting -- fears of further funding cuts!!! The Eagles banned from performing in Western Springs -- fears they may pick up musical vibes from old Split Enz concerts!! 
         </TD>
      <TD>Film at eleven...</TD>
      </TR>
      </TABLE>
    </TD>
    </TR> <!-- End of row 4 -->

