<TD></TD>
<TD><A href="wop.htm">The Weekly O'Press</A></TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<A NAME="About"></A><H2>About WebCentre</H2>

<P>WebCentre is <A HREF="../index.htm">our</A> soapbox, from which we earnestly seek to promote the development of responsive, readable and visitor-friendly Web sites in New Zealand. We do this with exhortations, cogent arguments, examples, a touch of humour and the odd bit of rabble rousing (which will naturally pass over the gentle reader).</P>
 
<P>Pet hates and jealousies are not excluded, but we've tried to mute our most trenchant criticisms in the full knowledge that the Web is a frontier, with sheriffs who never leave their office.</P>

<P>WebCentre is also where we (that is, <A HREF="../pin.htm#spis">SPIS Ltd)</A> get to talk about the sites we've done, are doing, and some of our plans for the future. But that's purely incidental.</P>

<P>So, without further ado...</P>

<A NAME="Sites We Made"></A><H2>A Selection of Sites We Have Made (or Remade)</H2>

<UL>
<LI><A href="www.wpm.co.nz/">Windpower Monthly Magazine</A> -- the world's premiere magazine for those in the business of windpower.

<LI><A HREF= "http://www.nettravel.co.nz/">NetTravel</A> -- a large, database-driven, searchable list of New Zealand accommodation providers, complete with a booking service, and substantial site automation and remote maintenance. Written for <A HREF="whynt.htm">Windows NT</A> using Borland Delphi and <A HREF="Webhub">Webhub.</A>

<LI><A HREF= "http://www.northland.ac.nz/nrc">Northland Regional Council</A>'s multi-level corporate site, with an explanation of what they do, a photo gallery, an educational section and general information about the Northland Region.

<LI><A HREF="http://www.chchpoly.ac.nz/">Christchurch Polytechnic's site</A>. The course and paper pages on this site are regularly generated from a database using <A HREF="webhub.htm">Webhub.</A>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.spis.co.nz/ssb/ssb.htm">South Sea Books,</A> a catalogue and ordering system for used and rare books. The catalogue is automatically updated every two months from the South Sea Books database.

<LI><A HREF="http://www.securicor.co.nz/">SecuriCor 3Net's</A> new corporate web site (formerly known as Network Dynamics)

<LI>The <A href="http://www.spis.co.nz/skeptics.htm">NZ Skeptics</A> -- the group to join if you're tired of New Age claptrap.</LI>

<LI>Takenaka Corporation's English language web site. As we have a long history of dealings in the Japanese market, it was natural that this huge Osaka-based architectural conglomerate would turn to us to make a quality English language site which nevertheless matched (and improved upon) the design standards of their Japanese site.<BR>
<I>(Still under development, in concert with our <A HREF="../pin.htm#MIR">partners</A> in Japan).</I>

</UL>

<A Name= "Sites We Like"></A><H2>Sites We Like</H2>

<P>Most of all, we like sites  that <strong>work</strong> rather than those which just have pretty pictures. But you'll get our attention if the pretty pictures are really <I>interesting,</I> -- like NASA's site for example.

<P>
<A href="http://www.altavista.digital.com/">Alta Vista</A> -- search the world's sites easily. The site we visit most often.<BR>
<A href="http://www.nasa.gov">NASA</A> -- lotsa cool stuff! And it works just fine with images off.<BR>
<A href="http://www.searchnz.co.nz/">SearchNZ</A> -- search all NZ sites easily, a "fuzzy" search
 engine, restricted to New Zealand cyberspace<BR>
</P>

<H2><a Name= "Sites We Hate">Sites We Loathe</A></H2>

<P>The slow ones, the badly spelt, the terrible HTML, the browser-specific, the unresponsive, the lousy navigation, the useless-with-images-off, the no feedback possible, the "must have frames"...</P>

<P><A href="http://wolf.co.net/index.html">Background tiles should not obscure the text</A>. And silly things to do with frames.<BR>
<A href="http://members.tripod.com/~baydolph/index.html">Shouting doesn't help get your message across</A>. Neither does blinking text.</P>

<P>We don't check these every week, so some may have improved since we added the link -- do <A HREF="mailto:peter@spis.co.nz">let us know...</A> If you'd care to nominate a site, we'd be happy to <A HREF="mailto:peter@spis.co.nz">hear about it.</A>
<P>And If you have a sick fascination with bad sites, check out <A href="http://www.mirsky.com/wow/">Mirsky's Worst of the Web</A>.

