<HEAD>
<TITLE>SPIS-- Editing and Media Services</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffcc" TEXT="#000099" >

<table width="100%">
<tr>
   <td><H1>SPIS Editing and Publishing Services</H1></td>
   <td width="16%"><A HREF="/spis/changes.htm">Last updated</A><BR>
      <!--Webber_Auto_StampDNR--><!--DS-->May  19 1996<!----></td>
   </tr>
</table>

<P><BIG><STRONG>SPIS</STRONG> doesn't just stand for South Pacific Information Services, it also stands for the prime assets we offer you:</BIG>

<TABLE Width="85%">
<TR>
   <TD Width="15%"><STRONG>Speed</STRONG></TD>
   <TD>We're fast at what we do, meeting deadlines with time to spare.</TD>
   </TR>
<TR>
   <TD><STRONG>Persistence</STRONG></TD>
   <TD>We don't give up on a job until it's <EM>right,</EM> even if it does mean working into the wee hours to meet those deadlines.</TD>
   </TR>
<TR>
   <TD><STRONG>Initiative</STRONG></TD>
   <TD>We've got the intelligence to check out queries or suggest better  alternatives, so we can provide the best possible service for you.</TD>
   </TR>
<TR>
   <TD><STRONG>Security</STRONG></TD>
   <TD>We offer the security of high quality, professional results -- without breaking the budget.</TD>
   </TR>
</TABLE>

<P>As well as producing the <A HREF="/spis/nzsm/nzsm.htm"><CITE>New Zealand Science Monthly,</CITE></A> we provide editing and publishing services to a number of community, professional and scientific organisations, within New Zealand and internationally.

<P>A combination of expert editing, professional typesetting, talented graphic designers and competitive printing rates allows us to provide a cost-effective publishing service, whether you want to produce a <A HREF="/spis/editserv.htm#NewsletterProduction">quarterly newsletter</A>, a flyer or a multi-volume set of <A HREF="/spis/editserv.htm#RelatedServices">conference proceedings.</A>

<P>We can even help with your <A HREF="/spis/softserv.htm">electronic publishing</A> and <A HREF="/spis/softserv.htm#WebPage">Web page design</A> needs.

<A NAME="NewsletterProduction"><H3>Newsletter production</H3></A>

<P>We provide targeted services. In producing the quarterly <CITE>New Zealand Science Review</CITE> for the <A HREF="mailto:mimrmb@wnmeds.ac.nz">New Zealand Association of Scientists,</A> we simply typeset to their specifications and print the final publication. For <CITE>HortTalk,</CITE> the bimonthly newsletter of the New Zealand Society for Horticultural Science, we source the stories, produce the newsletter and mail it out to members. For <A HREF="http://www.bitz.co.nz/straight/"><CITE>Straight Thinking</CITE></A> we handle the printing and distribution for its publisher, <A HREF="mailto:omcshane@deepthnk.kiwi.gen.nz">Owen McShane.</A>

<P>Our principal newsletter services include:

<!--Pending: links to NZAS and NZSHS, or information boxes about them (customers page)-->

<UL>
<LI>Article research and writing</LI>
<LI>Photography and illustrations</LI>
<LI>Editing for preferred style, grammar and readability</LI>
<LI>Design and layout</LI>
<LI>Typesetting</LI>
<LI>Printing</LI>
<LI>Distribution</LI>
<LI>Mailing list management</LI>
</UL>

<P>If you've got any other things you want done, <A HREF="mailto:nzsm@spis.co.nz">let us know</A> and we'll do it!

<!-- Pending: scanned, shrunk horttalk cover page?-->

<A NAME="DocumentReview"></A><H3>Document review and consultancy</H3>

<P>We provide consultancy services for clients who want their publications checked for readability, style, consistency and "oomph".

<P>Such services include:
<UL>
<LI>spelling, grammar and usage checks</LI>
<LI>advising on layout and design aspects</LI>
<LI>reviewing technical material to improve reader comprehension</LI>
<LI>adapting in-house reports for media releases</LI>
<LI>polishing promotional items for greater impact</LI>
</UL>

<P>Our rapid turnaround is enhanced by our 24-hour accessability via fax, modem and email. The finished work can be returned in the same manner, or we can go on to provide full editing and publishing services.

<P>The Canterbury Regional Council finds it useful to have us review the drafts of their technical reports. They know that they will get professional advice that improves their publications and enhances their reputation as a communicative organisation. We've also produced reader-friendly summaries of their often-massive documents, and have advised on how to spread the word on everything from eradicating nassella tussock to reducing city smog.

<!-- Pending: link to CRC if they have one -->

<A NAME="RelatedServices"><H3>Related services</H3></A>

<P>When you're running a conference, there's a hundred-and-one things to think about. We can make your job easier by handling your conference publishing, from initial announcements and flyers to programme production and publishing proceedings. Our experience and contacts can work to make it as simple and as economical as possible, so you can get on with the myriad other things you need to do.

<P>For the <EM>19th International Pyrotechnics Conference</EM>, we collated papers sent in from around the world (in both print and electronic form), to produce a 1.3-kilogram, hardbound text that matched the preceding 18 volumes.

<P>We offer transcription of taped conferences, meetings and seminars. As well as creating an accurate typed record of the event, we can go one step further by producing a fully edited and typeset report for distribution to attendees and other interested parties. Alternatively, we can fax or email the completed transcription directly to you with minimal delay.

<P>We've transcribed hours of material from multi-lingual conferences held in Japan, producing accurate records of highly technical seminars that have proved a bonus to conference attendees.

<HR>

<A NAME="MediaServices"></A><H2>Media Services</H2>

<P><BIG><STRONG>SPIS</STRONG> doesn't just stand for South Pacific Information Services, it also stands for how we work:</BIG>

<TABLE Width="85%">
<TR>
   <TD Width="15%"><STRONG>Savvy</STRONG></TD>
   <TD>We know how the media work and which buttons to push.</TD>
   </TR>
<TR>
   <TD><STRONG>Professional</STRONG></TD>
   <TD>We're professionals in the media world, working to a professional standard.</TD>
   </TR>
<TR>
   <TD><STRONG>Informed</STRONG></TD>
   <TD>We know what's likely to attract attention, and how to make your media relations work for you.</TD>
   </TR>
<TR>
   <TD><STRONG>Set up</STRONG></TD>
   <TD>We've got the right set-up to make swift contact with whatever media outlets you want.</TD>
   </TR>
</TABLE>

<P>We're a media-based organisation and we've learnt the best ways of presenting material to the rest of the Fourth Estate. The tricks of the trade are many and varied, and you have to know the difference between a press release and a feature story, what is news and what isn't, how to present your material -- and yourself -- appropriately to get your message across. We can help you do that through the range of media services we offer.

<A NAME="MediaLiaison"></A><H3>Media liaison</H3>

<P>SPIS has close links with other media organisations and considerable experience in producing feature articles and press releases which get attention in both print and broadcast media. We know how to write material that the media will want to use.

<P>That's because we do a lot of writing and broadcasting ourselves. Since our inception, we've provided news and feature articles on a regular basis to more than a dozen publications and numerous broadcast outlets, in New Zealand and around the world. There's news items on the New Zealand wind energy scene, produced for the Danish magazine <CITE>Windpower Monthly</CITE>,
<!-- Pending: WPM link here --> a monthly astronomy column for the <CITE>New Zealand Herald</CITE>, the eighth year of the Momentum science column in Japan's <A HREF="http://www.yomiuri.co.jp/index-e.htm"><CITE>Daily Yomiuri</CITE></A>, and the monthly science slot on Alison Parr's Sunday show on National Radio.

<P>We can help you get better press coverage and establish more effective media relationships by helping you to:
<UL>
<LI>Research, write and distribute media releases on a regular basis</LI>
<LI>Prepare feature articles about specific initiatives or products</LI>
<LI>Field and answer media enquiries</LI>
<LI>Plan and organise media days and events</LI>
</UL>

<A NAME="MediaTraining"><H3>Media training</H3></A>

<P>We can provide seminars and training materials to better equip you and your staff to deal with the media. We can give you the skills to look at your own media relations and see how they can be improved. We can help you develop better media management over a range of areas, including:
<UL>
<LI>Identifying your target media and building press relations</LI>
<LI>Analysing your press releases to identify weak points and make them effective</LI>
<LI>Interview preparation for print and broadcast media</LI>
</UL>

