<HEAD>
<TITLE>Ros and the SCA</TITLE>

</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#99DDFF"><H1 align="center">My Alter Ego from the Middle Ages</H1>
<HR align="center">

<P>The hobby that takes up much of my time and money is the Society for Creative Anachronism. Within this group I am known as Madelein Cer&eacute;is de Toulouse, a 15th Century Frenchwoman of Spanish ancestry.</P>

<P>I belong to the <A href="/spis/phil/southron.htm">Barony of Southron Gaard</A> in the fair Kingdom of Caid. I have been Chatelaine, Seneschal, and Exchequer for this group over the past seven years, and am currently the local Minister for Children. In March 1996 I was greatly privileged to be made a member of the Order of the Pelican.</P>

<P>My interests are:</P>

<TABLE width="75%">
<TR>
<TD align=left>
<UL><LI>Embroidery</LI>
<LI><UL><LI>Split Stitch</LI>
<LI>Counted thread (especially Blackwork)</LI></UL></LI>
<LI>Sewing</LI>
<LI>Dancing</LI>
<LI>Games</LI>
<LI><UL><LI>Backgammon</LI>
<LI>Playing with children</LI></UL></LI>
<LI>Music</LI>
<LI><UL><LI>Singing</LI>
<LI>Playing recorder</LI>
<LI>Playing guitar</LI></UL></LI>
</UL>
</TD>
<TD valign=middle align=left>
<IMG src="images/ros.gif" alt="Madelein's Arms" align="Right" height="100" width="95">
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<P><A HREF="mailto:tanuki@takamori.southern.co.nz">Mail me</A> if you want to talk to me about any interests you share, or if you have any tips and ideas about working with children in the SCA.</P>

